sql:
SELECT namespace_id, SUM(duration_ms) AS total_duration
FROM ges_operations
GROUP BY namespace_id;

SELECT namespace_id, AVG(ges_lock_requests) AS avg_lock_requests
FROM real_time_monitoring
GROUP BY namespace_id;

SELECT LOWER(namespace_name) AS lower_namespace_name
FROM namespaces
WHERE namespace_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'left their mark' refers to users who have resolved alerts; 
- 'visit duration' refers to access_duration in access_logs; 
- 'milestones' refers to alerts resolved by users; 
- 'made their presence known' refers to users having at least one access session recorded in access_logs.

sql:
SELECT AVG(duration_ms) AS average_duration
FROM ges_operations
WHERE namespace_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- GES operations refer to Global Enqueue Service operations which are vital for managing and monitoring database resources. These include lock requests, pin requests, pin releases, invalidation requests, and actual invalidations; 
- A namespace in this context refers to an organizational unit in a database or system, which can be used to categorize or group related data or objects; 
- Real-time and historical data refer to the current (real-time) and past (historical) system monitoring data, respectively; 
- User activity metrics (access count and total access duration) are important for understanding how users interact with the system or database; 
- Alerts (total and active) are notifications about potentially critical system events or conditions that require attention.
